{
  "texts": [
    "At the output plane, another 4-f lens set (L3 and L4) is used to image the outputs onto the SLM3, which, together with the third 4-f imaging system, a collimator, a single-mode fiber, and the superconducting nanowire single-photon detector (Eos4 of Single Quantum, 70% efficiency at 1550 nm, ~300 dark counts), constitute a spatial mode analyzer.",
    "A multichannel picosecond event timer (HydraHarp 400 of PicoQuant) is used to record all detector clicks for later analysis."
  ]
}